---
# clang-analyzer-security.insecureAPI.*:
#     Recommends Annex K `_s` variants (memset_s, snprintf_s, ...) that
#     are not implemented by glibc and are widely considered a failed
#     extension. We use bounds-checking forms (snprintf/vsnprintf with
#     explicit sizes) which is the right answer for portable C11.
#
# clang-analyzer-valist.Uninitialized:
#     False positive on var-arg helpers that immediately follow
#     `va_start`. Triggers on every error-formatting helper.
Checks: '-clang-analyzer-security.insecureAPI.*,-clang-analyzer-valist.Uninitialized'
